_:Bbd2db0fa52d47a39f6cd73c9d1cd0b6e <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "Muscle tissue which is unstriated, composed primarily of smooth muscle fibers surrounded by a reticulum of collagen and elastic fibers. Smooth muscle differs from striated muscle in the much higher actin/myosin ratio, the absence of conspicuous sarcomeres and the ability to contract to a much smaller fraction of its resting length[GO]." <https://purl.wholepersonphysiome.org/wpp/muscular-system> .
